It is required to write your own **TableCell**.
For example, I can provide my one, which, depending on the stored value, displays different pictures in the cell. In the *setGraphic* method, you can set any javaFX element.

```
public class IncreaseTableCell extends TableCell&lt;Position, Boolean&gt; {

    public IncreaseTableCell() {
        super();
    }

    public static Callback&lt;TableColumn&lt;Position, Boolean&gt;, TableCell&lt;Position, Boolean&gt;&gt;
    getCellFactory() {
        return e -&gt; {
            IncreaseTableCell cell = new IncreaseTableCell();
            cell.setAlignment(Pos.CENTER);
            return cell;
        };
    }

    @Override
    protected void updateItem(Boolean item, boolean empty) {
        super.updateItem(item, empty);

        if (item != null)
            setGraphic(StructureGUI.getIcon(item ? &quot;up&quot; : &quot;down&quot;));
    }
}
```

Further, to use the written TableCell in table, it is required to add when setting up the table:

```
column.setCellFactory(IncreaseTableCell.getCellFactory());
```

